age, AoW Monk Legs x2, CCoM, ... 4/22</span><hr size=1> Rather than flame Mr. Nose for his implication that there are shady, underhanded means of making the amount of plat that Griz is selling his stuff for, I'll provide one answer to the question he seems to be asking..<br>
<br>
Now I'm not the bazaar maestro that Griz is, I'm just a smith.  I GM'd my smithing in February of last year and have made my money from that, sometimes in buckets and sometimes in cups.  I hit GM just as Luclin came out, and with it the BD armor and the PoTC quest.  My partner and I probably sold about 600-700 sickles last year between when Luclin came out and the end of the year.  The sale price for most of last year was 2k each, of which about 1200pp was profit.  Multiply that by 700 and you have 840kpp.  Add in the sales of the dorf BD armor I've made (not many, but I've made the occasional sale), and my partner and I estimate we've made about 600-750kpp each in profits over the last year since Luclin came out (we split all profits 50/50).<br>
<br>
Again, this is not the kinda money it would take to be the bazaar merchant prince that Griz is, but it is still a pretty hefty chunk of change.  And while the PoTC market has slowed down the last few months (while at the same time the number of smiths making sickles has gone up...), and almost all of that money I've blown buying equipment, twinking alts, and helping out friends, at one time my partner and I had between us enough money to take a stab at some of Griz's higher priced items.<br>
<br>
Just one sooper sekrit method of making the kind of plat you are talking about, Mr. Nose.  Hopefully it helps to rest your fears that all of us rich folks are conspiring to keep all the money in our hands, and that our GM buddies and relatives aren't trying to keep you poor. <p>Pavel Cursebreaker<br>
250 Smith<br>
